2 MLR¶

In [8]:
reg = lm(unlist(y)~X)
In [9]:
s_reg=summary(reg)
a_reg=anova(reg)
SST=sum((a_reg$'Sum Sq')[1:length(a_reg$'Sum Sq')])

c.di=cooks.distance(reg) #cooksd
hii=lm.influence(reg)$hat #leverages
ei=residuals(reg) #Residuals
di=studres(reg) #studentized Residuals
press_res=ei/(1-hii) #press resids
PRESS=sum(press_res^2) #PRESS score

#r2
r2=s_reg$r.squared
r2_adj=s_reg$adj.r.squared
r2_pred=1-PRESS/SST
In [10]:

transformation_func=list(
  function(x) x^-4,
  function(x) x^-3,
  function(x) x^-2,
  function(x) x^-1,
  function(x) x^-0.5,
  function(x) x^0.5,
  function(x) x,
  function(x) x^2,
  function(x) x^3,
  function(x) x^4,
  function(x) log(x),
  function(x) exp(x),
  function(x) ((x-mean(x))^2),
  function(x) ((x-mean(x))^3)
  
)

corr_func=function(x, y){
  xs=sapply(1:14, function(t) transformation_func[[t]](x))
  apply(xs, 2, function(x) cor(x,y))
  
}

MVN normality check for residuals

In [23]:
n = dim(residuals)[1]
p = dim(residuals)[2]
S = cov(residuals)
x_bar = colMeans(residuals)
d2_hat = get_d2(residuals, x_bar, S)

Principal Components vs. Observations: We plotted violin plots (with boxplot) of first 6 PC's and spotted outliers. They explain a total 85% variance (look scree plot)

In [32]:
mm = 9
PCA6 = PCA$PrincipalComponents[,1:mm]
labes = paste("PC", rep(c(1:mm), each = 60), sep="")
obs = rep(c(1:60), mm)
df = data.frame(Value = as.vector(PCA6), PrincipalComponent = labes, obs = obs)

is_outlier <- function(x) {
    return(x < quantile(x, 0.25) - 1.9 * IQR(x) | x > quantile(x, 0.75) + 1.9 * IQR(x))
}

df %>%
    group_by(PrincipalComponent) %>%
        mutate(outlier = ifelse(is_outlier(Value), obs, as.numeric(NA))) %>%
            ggplot(., aes(x = factor(PrincipalComponent), y = Value, fill = factor(PrincipalComponent))) +
                geom_violin() + geom_boxplot(width=0.3, fill = "white")+ theme(legend.position = "NULL") +
                geom_text(aes(label = outlier), na.rm = TRUE, hjust = -1, size = 4) + xlab("")+ylab("")

Fit functions for models¶

all 3 functions returns 2 objets
preds: prediction performance model: fitted model class

Multinomial logistic L2 regularization, softmax¶

In [64]:
get_pred_multinom = function(trainMy, testMy, mySeed){
    set.seed(mySeed)
    x = trainMy[,-1]
    y = trainMy$Region
    x = data.matrix(x)
    xtest = data.matrix(testMy[,-1])

    multinom_model = cv.glmnet(x, y, family="multinomial", type.multinomial = "grouped", parallel = TRUE)
    mm_pred = predict(multinom_model, newx = xtest, s = "lambda.1se", type = "class")
    mm_pred = as.vector(mm_pred)
    GroundT =  unlist(testMy[,1])
    a = confusionMatrix(data = mm_pred, reference = GroundT) 
    return(list(preds = as.vector(c(round(a$overall[1],2),a$byClass[,1])), model = multinom_model))
}

Neural net 2 hidden layers¶

In [66]:
get_pred_neuralnet = function(trainMy, testMy, mySeed){
    
    use_session_with_seed(mySeed)
    #data prepare#############
    x_train = as.matrix(trainMy[,-1])
    y_train = trainMy[,1]
    x_test = as.matrix(testMy[,-1])
    y_test = testMy[,1]
    x_train = apply(x_train, 2, function(x) (x -min(x))/(max(x)-min(x)))
    y_train = to_categorical(as.factor(y_train), 5)[,-1]
    x_test = apply(x_test, 2, function(x) (x -min(x))/(max(x)-min(x)))
    y_test = to_categorical(as.factor(y_test), 5)[,-1]
                  
    #model build#############
    model <- keras_model_sequential()
    model %>% 

      layer_dense(units = 10,
                  input_shape = c(15), 
                  kernel_regularizer = regularizer_l2(l = 0.1)) %>% 

      layer_batch_normalization() %>% 
      layer_activation("relu")%>% 
      layer_dropout(0.5) %>% 

      layer_dense(units = 10,
                  kernel_regularizer = regularizer_l2(l = 0.1)) %>% 

      layer_batch_normalization() %>% 
      layer_activation("relu")%>% 
      layer_dropout(0.5) %>% 

      layer_dense(units = 4, activation = 'softmax')
                   
    #model compile#############
    model %>% compile(
        loss = 'categorical_crossentropy',
        optimizer = optimizer_adam(),
        metrics = c('accuracy')
        )
                   
    #model fit#############
    epochs = 500
    history <- model %>% fit(
      x_train, y_train,
      batch_size = 5,
      callback_model_checkpoint("C:/Users/enes/Desktop/checkpoints.h5", monitor = "val_acc", save_best_only = T),
      epochs = epochs,
      validation_data = list(x_test, y_test),
      verbose = 0
    )
                   
    model = load_model_hdf5("C:/Users/enes/Desktop/checkpoints.h5")
                   
    GroundT =  unlist(testMy[,1])
    mlp_pred <- model %>% predict_classes(x_test)
    mlp_pred = ur[model %>% predict_classes(x_test)+1]
                   
    a = confusionMatrix(data = mlp_pred, reference = GroundT)
    return(list(preds = as.vector(c(round(a$overall[1],2),a$byClass[,1])), model = history))
}

In [69]:
get_pred_dectree = function(trainMy, testMy, mySeed){
    dt_fit = rpart(Region~., method="class", data = trainMy)
    dt_pred = predict(dt_fit, testMy[,-1])
    dt_pred = ur[apply(dt_pred, 1, which.max)]
    
    GroundT =  unlist(testMy[,1])
    a = confusionMatrix(data = dt_pred, reference = GroundT) 
    return(list(preds = as.vector(c(round(a$overall[1],2),a$byClass[,1])), model = dt_fit))
}

get_pred_knn = function(trainMy, testMy, mySeed){
    set.seed(mySeed)

    cl <- factor(unlist(trainMy[,1]))

    knn_pred = kknn(Region~., trainMy, testMy, k = 7)
    knn_pred <- fitted(knn_pred)

    GroundT =  unlist(testMy[,1])
    a = confusionMatrix(data = knn_pred, reference = GroundT) 
    return(list(preds = as.vector(c(round(a$overall[1],2),a$byClass[,1])), model = NULL))
}
